The Royal Bank Of Scotland plc Key Developments

The Royal Bank of Scotland plc Announces Redemption of the Notes
Feb 28 17
The Royal Bank of Scotland plc announced that, the holders of the AUD 883,419,000 Subordinated Fixed to Fixed Rate Notes due 2022 Callable 2017; CAD 420,199,000 Subordinated Fixed to Fixed Rate Notes due 2022 Callable 2017; EUR 563,801,000 Subordinated Fixed to Fixed Rate Notes due 2022 Callable 2017; USD 2,132,059,000 Subordinated Fixed to Fixed Rate Notes due 2022 Callable 2017; CHF 124,452,000 Subordinated Fixed to Fixed Rate Notes due 2022 Callable 2017 have been notified by the company of the upcoming redemption of the Notes (other than the Australian Dollar Notes) on 16 March 2017 and the Australian Dollar Notes on 19 March 2017. The amount of the Australian Dollar Notes, Canadian Dollar Notes, Euro Notes, U.S. Dollar Notes and CHF Notes currently outstanding is AUD 883,419,000.00, CAD 420,199,000.00, EUR 563,801,000.00, USD 2,132,059,000.00 and CHF 124,452,000.00, respectively. Terms used but not defined herein shall have the meaning given to them in the notice of redemption. The Notes are being redeemed pursuant to Condition 5(d) of the Notes (Call Option - Redemption at the Option of the Issuer) at par, together with interest accrued to (but excluding) the Redemption Date (in the case of the Notes other than the Australian Dollar Notes) and the Australian Dollar Notes Redemption Date (in the case of the Australian Dollar Notes). The Issuer has notified the holders pursuant to the terms of the Notes.


The Royal Bank of Scotland plc Reports Consolidated Earnings Results and Bank Cash Flow Results for the Year Ended December 31, 2016
Feb 24 17
The Royal Bank of Scotland plc reported consolidated earnings results and bank cash flow results for the year ended December 31, 2016. For the year, the company reported net interest income of £8,288 million compared to £8,282 million a year ago. Total income was £12,123 million compared to £11,939 million a year ago. Operating loss before tax was £3,732 million compared to £3,234 million a year ago. Loss from continuing operations was £4,880 million compared to £3,182 million a year ago. Loss attributable to ordinary shareholders was £1,950 million compared to £3,234 million a year ago. Net cash flow from operating activities was £6,969 million compared to £1,122 million a year ago. Purchase of property, plant and equipment was £902 million compared to £761 million a year ago.

For the year, on bank basis, the company reported net cash flow from operating activities of £3,098 million compared to £5,488 million a year ago. Purchase of property, plant and equipment was £508 million compared to £328 million a year ago.


The Royal Bank Of Scotland plc Reports Consolidated Earnings Results for the Half Year Ended June 30, 2016
Aug 5 16
The Royal Bank Of Scotland plc reported consolidated earnings results for the half year ended June 30, 2016. For the period, the company reported net interest income of £4,192 million, total income of £5,833 million, operating profit before tax of £218 million and net loss attributable to ordinary shareholders was £108 million against net interest income of £4,245 million, total income of £6,786 million, operating loss before tax of £147 million and net loss attributable to ordinary shareholders was £358 million a year ago. Loss from continuing operations was £83 million compared to £390 million a year ago. Net cash flows used in operating activities was £4,892 million compared to net cash flows from operating activities of £9,663 million a year ago.


